#Text=Actor Doris Day dies at 97
#Text=Thursday , May 16 , 2019
#Text=US singer , actor , and animal rights advocate Doris Day died on Monday at her home in Carmel Valley , California .
#Text=Day made many studio albums , was awarded the Presidential Medal of Freedom , and rescued animals from Hurricane Katrina .
#Text=Day 's animal foundation said she had been in otherwise " excellent physical health for her age " but had recently had pneumonia .

#Text=Reportedly , her name was shortened to  Doris Day , " imitating a song called " Day after Day , " so it would fit on a sign .

column1: #Text=Over the course of her singing career , Day made 29 studio albums and performed live with big bands , such as Les Brown and His Band of Renown .
#Text=Day was paid more than any other female singer by 1946 .
#Text=In film , she was successful in romantic comedies and musicals .

#Text=Though she was nominated for the Oscar for the 1959 romantic comedy Pillow Talk , opposite Rock Hudson , Day personally considered her best film performance to be her portrayal of singer Ruth Etting in the James Cagney film Love Me or Leave Me .
#Text=She also performed in a film by director Alfred Hitchcock , The Man Who Knew Too Much .
#Text=Poster for the 1956 film The Man Who Knew Too Much .
#Text=Image : Paramount Pictures , Inc. .
#Text=For much of her career , Day presented a very wholesome image .

#Text=" I have the unfortunate reputation of being Miss Goody Two-Shoes , America 's Virgin , and all that , " Day said in her 1976 autobiography , " so I 'm afraid it 's going to shock some people for me to say this , but I staunchly believe no two people should get married until they have lived together[ . ]
